                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240114-218-off1234 t18240114-218-crimeloc1237"></join>. On the 13th of January, I was at work at a house there, and left about half-past eight o'clock; I had locked the door; returned about nine, and found the staple drawn and the prisoner in the house; he had been painting there about a week before. He asked if his partner was there; I said No. He went away, saying he would see if he was in the other house, and in about a quarter of an hour I missed two squares and went to the other house, but he was not there.</p>
